@api_HostAddress = http://localhost:5204
@token = YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### ============================================
### AUTHENTICATION ENDPOINTS
### ============================================

### 1. Register - Créer un nouveau compte
POST {{api_HostAddress}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "Test123!",
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Doe"
}

### 2. Login - Se connecter (récupérer le token)
POST {{api_HostAddress}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "Test123!"
}

### 3. Get Current User - Tester l'authentification (nécessite un token)
GET {{api_HostAddress}}/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ============================================
### WEATHER FORECAST ENDPOINTS (Authentification requise)
### ============================================

### 4. GET All WeatherForecasts - Récupérer toutes les prévisions
GET {{api_HostAddress}}/api/weatherforecast
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### 5. GET WeatherForecast by ID - Récupérer une prévision par ID
GET {{api_HostAddress}}/api/weatherforecast/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### 6. POST WeatherForecast - Créer une nouvelle prévision
POST {{api_HostAddress}}/api/weatherforecast
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "date": "2025-01-15T00:00:00",
  "temperatureC": 25,
  "summary": "Sunny"
}

### 7. PUT WeatherForecast - Mettre à jour une prévision existante
PUT {{api_HostAddress}}/api/weatherforecast/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": 1,
  "date": "2025-01-15T00:00:00",
  "temperatureC": 30,
  "summary": "Very Sunny"
}

### 8. DELETE WeatherForecast - Supprimer une prévision
DELETE {{api_HostAddress}}/api/weatherforecast/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ============================================
### TESTS RAPIDES
### ============================================

### Test complet : Register → Login → Create Forecast
